"danger_power_title" = "Installing socket fuses";
"danger_power_text" = "Baby and child fingers fit exactly into the holes of the socket. Therefore, there is a particular risk of fatal electric shock. Use socket protectors that can prevent this. Little crawlers are sure to immediately find the unsecured sockets in your home.";
"danger_toiletwater_title" = "Close WC lid";
"danger_toiletwater_text" = "Children can drown even in very low water and especially colorful toilet stones animate mice to try them. You can prevent both with a toilet lid safety device. So %1$s can neither fall in nor eat the poisonous toilet stone.";
"danger_furniture_tipover_title" = "Attach anti-tilt device for furniture";
"danger_furniture_tipover_text" = "When little ones become mobile, they try to hold on to everything and climb up. Furniture can tip over and fall on %1$s as a result. An anti-tip device for furniture can prevent the worst from happening. Large appliances, such as a TV, could also tip over and fall onto %1$s. Try to secure them with the help of the anti-tip device as well.";
"danger_furniture_fallingof_title" = "Remove tablecloths";
"danger_furniture_fallingof_text" = "During their first attempts at walking, %1$s will hold on to anything that is not nailed down. Tablecloths in particular are very dangerous, as the little ones can not only injure themselves on the falling objects, but can also scald themselves with the hot soup, for example. Therefore, do not use tablecloths and check which objects %1$s could hurt when falling down.";
"danger_furniture_edges_title" = "Protect corners and edges";
"danger_furniture_edges_text" = "The little gym mice can quickly hit their heads on corners and edges when learning to walk or when playing. To prevent injuries, use a corner and/or edge protector.";
"danger_furniture_drawer_title" = "Lock drawers";
"danger_furniture_drawer_text" = "Drawers can bring several dangers at once: on the one hand, of course, they are a climbing aid for %1$s, but also interesting and dangerous. Small children's fingers can quickly become trapped in the drawer. That hurts! Smart remedies are magnetic locks.";
"danger_plant_poison_title" = "Remove poisonous plants";
"danger_plant_poison_text" = "Some plants are poisonous. Fruits, leaves and flowers can cause poisoning if eaten. Other plants secrete liquid, which can be dangerous to %1$s. If you are unsure, consult a plant guide, ask at your local nursery, or use your own plant identification apps. The safest thing to do is to remove the plants.";
"danger_plant_sting_title" = "prickly plants out of reach";
"danger_plant_sting_text" = "Some plants have thorns or spines. To prevent the little gnomes from pricking their fingers, it is best to place them out of reach of %1$s.";
"danger_plant_soil_title" = "Make plant soil inaccessible";
"danger_plant_soil_text" = "Potting soil or granules usually contain fertilizers and are therefore harmful to %1$s. Stretch a plant protection net over the pot and the soil and protect small plant explorers from poisoning.";
"danger_washingmachine_title" = "Lock washing machine";
"danger_washingmachine_text" = "The washing machine or clothes dryer are often used by children as a hiding place. It is especially dangerous when the door falls into the lock behind %1$s. With a universal lock, the door remains closed and does not provide a hiding place.";
"danger_radiator_title" = "Protect hot radiators";
"danger_radiator_text" = "Attention hot! Radiators and pipes become very hot and can cause burns. Pipes could be insulated. Maybe you can also make the radiator inaccessible for %1$s.";
"danger_lightbulb_title" = "Eliminate hot light fixtures";
"danger_lightbulb_text" = "Conventional light bulbs or halogen lamps get hot. Protect your child's fingers and do something good for the environment: LED lamps do not get hot and are also energy-saving.";
"danger_door_pinch_title" = "Prevent jamming at door";
"danger_door_pinch_text" = "Trapped fingers in doors are one of the most common injuries. You can use a foam doorstop to prevent %1$s from getting their fingers caught in the door. Be careful not to use heavy door stops for the floor, as little ones could get hurt with them. The foam doorstops are specially designed for children.";
"danger_door_pinchback_title" = "Preventing pinching on door hinges";
"danger_door_pinchback_text" = "There is also a risk of pinching little children's fingers on the hinge side of a door. A pinch guard can reduce this risk.";
"danger_door_lockout_title" = "Securely lock front door";
"danger_door_lockout_text" = "Especially in the case of front doors, there is also the danger that the little mice lock themselves out unnoticed. A door lock can prevent %1$s from opening the door.";
"danger_window_title" = "Fenstersturz verhindern";
"danger_window_text" = "Falls from the window are life-threatening. You can prevent this with window and balcony door safety devices. Also make sure that the little ones cannot crawl onto the windowsill.";
"danger_stairs_title" = "Prevent fall on stairs";
"danger_stairs_text" = "When the little world explorers become mobile, they are magically attracted to stairs. To prevent %1$s falling down the stairs, a stair gate can help banish this danger. But it can also help to keep the little ones away from other dangers.";
"danger_hotwater_title" = "Avoid scalding by hot water";
"danger_hotwater_text" = "Hot water can %1$s cause severe scalding. A remedy is a faucet with integrated mixed water shut-off and safety lock. You can also lower the heating temperature of your hot water boiler to prevent severe scalding.";
"danger_boiler_title" = "Ensure clean drinking water";
"danger_boiler_text" = "If you lower the heating temperature to avoid scalding, this can lead to the formation of bacteria such as legionella, which can harm you and your family. But also old pipes can contaminate the drinking water. You can check the quality of your drinking water by regular water tests.";
"danger_cleaning_supplies_title" = "Safely lock chemicals";
"danger_cleaning_supplies_text" = "Detergents, cleaning products, and cosmetics contain chemicals that are unproper or dangerous for %1$s, especially if they get into the eyes or mouth. Sometimes the containers have a safety cap, but it is better to store them out of reach of the little ones. If this is not possible, you can also lock the cabinets with a magnetic lock.";
"danger_sofa_title" = "Prevent sofa / bed fall";
"danger_sofa_text" = "To prevent %1$s from injuring themselves by falling off the bed or sofa, you should not leave %1$s unattended. To prevent %1$s from falling off the bed, you can use a height-adjustable grate. However, keep in mind that older children often crawl over the grille as well, increasing the height at which they fall and the risk of injury. So use bed rails only as long as it makes sense.";
"danger_oven_title" = "Secure stove";
"danger_oven_text" = "On the hot stove top, %1$s can burn themselves very quickly and even catch %1$s the handle of a cooking pot. There is a risk of severe scalding with hot contents. To prevent this, a safety grid for the stove can be helpful. If you don't want to use a grid, try to always turn the handle of your pots and pans backwards out of reach.";
"danger_ovenswitch_title" = "Secure stove knobs";
"danger_ovenswitch_text" = "The little kitchen helpers like to play with the knobs on the stove. But if the hotplate is turned on unnoticed, the entire kitchen can quickly catch fire. The appropriate fuses can prevent %1$s from turning it.";
"danger_ropes_title" = "Remove curtain cords and other ropes";
"danger_ropes_text" = "Ropes, cords, chains, cables but also curtains longer than 22cm is a danger for %1$s. The little ones like to wrap these things around their head or neck and can strangle themselves. Therefore, make sure to secure these things well in your home.";
"danger_candle_title" = "Avoid candles and scented oils";
"danger_candle_text" = "Candles and fire are always a danger, of course. Since %1$s can get burned by them, you should keep them out of reach. You should always use candles and scented oils with babies only with caution, because the little noses are very sensitive. If you do not want to do without them, choose organic oils or use an organic room spray instead.";
"danger_hair_title" = "Avoid Tourniquet Syndrome";
"danger_hair_text" = "Long hairs can wrap around your baby's fingers or toes and cut off the blood supply, causing fingers or toes to die. In technical terms, this is called Tourniquet syndrome. Keep checking your baby's fingers and toes.";
"danger_railing_title" = "Secure railing with bars with plexiglass";
"danger_railing_text" = "When using a grille or railing, make sure that the bars are no more than 65 mm apart. This way you can be sure that your child's head will not get stuck and %1$s will not suffocate. You can use plexiglass if the distance is greater.";
"danger_dishwasher_title" = "Secure dishwasher";
"danger_dishwasher_text" = "The little kitchen helpers can get scalded by hot steam when the dishwasher door is opened. If your dishwasher doesn't have an automatic shut-off, the hot water can also cause scalding. Here you can help yourself with universal latches, so %1$s can not open the dishwasher just like that.";
"danger_cable_title" = "Cable out of range";
"danger_cable_text" = "The little explorers of the world like to put everything in their mouths and chew on it - especially when they are teething. Even cables are not safe from their mouths. These are not only dangerous because the little ones can strangle themselves with them - even when biting on a cable %1$s can suffer a fatal electric shock. Cable hoses can help keep the cables safely wrapped.";
"danger_pool_title" = "Secure pool and paddling pool";
"danger_pool_text" = "Pools and wading pools are particularly dangerous for little non-swimmers. Small children can drown in water that is only a few centimeters deep. Therefore, make sure that pools and paddling pools are inaccessible for %1$s.";
"danger_knife_title" = "Clear away sharp and pointed objects";
"danger_knife_text" = "Sharp and pointed objects can %1$s naturally hurt themselves if they handle them without your supervision. Therefore, do not leave knives, forks, scissors, tools and other sharp or pointed objects in your home, but keep them safe.";
"danger_bag_title" = "Plastic bags out of reach";
"danger_bag_text" = "Plastic bags are not only harmful to our environment, but can also be dangerous to our young children. If %1$s put a plastic bag over their head, %1$s can easily choke on it. Therefore, keep plastic bags out of reach or use cloth bags instead.";
"danger_toy_title" = "Check toys for harmful substances";
"danger_toy_text" = "Yes, even children's toys can be dangerous for %1$s. On the one hand, if they are not suitable for the age of your child, on the other hand, if they contain dangerous pollutants and plasticizers that are dangerous for %1$s in the long term. So when buying toys, look carefully at what materials the toy is made of and try to prefer natural materials.";
"danger_smallitems_title" = "Store small parts out of reach";
"danger_smallitems_text %@ %@" = "The little world explorers first check their surroundings with their mouths, so any find goes right there first. In the worst case, the item clogs the airways and %@ can choke on it. If %@ swallows the objects, in the best case they come to light again after some time, but can cause some damage in the body. Therefore, try to keep all small, round objects out of reach of your pet.";
"danger_weapons_title" = "Lock weapons";
"danger_weapons_text %@" = "It is undisputed that weapons are not for children. Lock up firearms and stabbing weapons, but also batons and the like well in front of your no treasure. After all, you don't want %@ to play with them and hurt or even kill themselves or others.";
"danger_battery_title" = "Batteries out of range";
"danger_battery_text" = "Batteries, especially button batteries, should be kept safe from your child. Because if %1$s swallows them, it's an emergency and you need to go to the hospital immediately. Button cells can cause serious damage to your favorite's esophagus.";
"danger_cutlery_title" = "Use children's cutlery";
"danger_cutlery_text" = "Knife, fork, scissors, light are not for small children! - says already an old proverb. The danger with cutlery is mainly the tips of the fork and even with sharp knives can %1$s hurt. However, the youngest children like to use cutlery like the grown-ups. Therefore, special children's cutlery with rounded tips and blunt knives is suitable.";
"danger_cover_title" = "Create pad and blanket free sleeping environment";
"danger_cover_text" = "For babies, blankets and bolsters also pose some danger, as they cannot free themselves if the bolster and blanket lands on their face. So if %1$s is still very small, avoid cushions and blankets when sleeping and when %1$s is unattended.";
"danger_mirror_title" = "Protect mirrors and glass from breakage";
"danger_mirror_text" = "Mirrors or glass plates pose a great danger, especially if they break. So that %1$s do not hurt themselves on the splinters, you can already make sure when buying that you buy shatterproof mirrors. Especially for the children's room, these are more suitable. If you want to be on the safe side, you can also cover existing mirrors or glass surfaces with a special film.";
"danger_fireplace_title" = "Secure fireplaces";
"danger_fireplace_text" = "To %1$s protect against burns from a fireplace or other fireplace in your home, a grate is certainly very helpful. Unfortunately, normal grates are not suitable for this purpose, as they are often made of wood or plastic. A heat resistant safety grate will protect little curious kids from dangerous burns from fireplaces.";
